<TEXT>
indiana state health commissioner dr woodrow a 
myers jr was named new york citys top health official friday 
despite opposition to his aids policies by gay rights activists and 
a prominent aids researcher 
mayor david n dinkins announced the appointment of myers as 
city health commissioner just one day after several supporters on a 
search committee withdrew their backing among those who stopped 
supporting myers was dr mathilde krim cofounder of the american 
foundation on aids research 
myers supports indiana laws to keep government lists of those 
infected with the aids virus and to quarantine people who knowingly 
infect others 
the indiana official has said he wouldnt impose such policies 
in new york and would support the policies of dinkins who opposes 
quarantines and government lists 
despite the controversial aids policies in indiana myers has a 
national reputation as an aids expert he is credited with 
encouraging indiana doctors to treat aids patients and was 
instrumental in arranging schooling for ryan white a teenage 
aidsafflicted hemopheliac who received national attention when a 
local school board refused to enroll him 
myers also made headlines by resigning from his post as vice 
chairman of the presidents commission on hiv under ronald reagan 
to protest what he said were inadequacies with the group hiv or 
the human immunodeficiency virus causes aids 
on thursday krim and several other members of the search 
committee withdrew support from him krim cited profound 
differences between myers views and desirable public health 
policies 
im not the insensitive brutish fiend that some people have 
tried to make me out to be myers said this week 
myers on friday underscored that saying quarantine is not an 
effective health strategy 
myers 35 will earn 110000 a year as commissioner and also 
get an annual 22000 supplement as an assistant professor of 
medicine at the cornell university medical school 
in outlining the challenges facing the appointee dinkins 
referred to a recent study that found a man in bangladesh has a 
better chance of living past age 40 than a man in harlem 
the causes of this shocking finding will set the agenda for 
the new health commissioner drug and alcohol abuse cirrhosis 
violence and the spread of disease including the aids epidemic 
dinkins said 
there have been 23000 aids cases in new york and 12000 have 
died at least 200000 new yorkers and perhaps nearly twice that 
many have been infected with the virus 
protests continued friday afternoon with about 75 members of 
the aids coalition to unleash power picketing in front of city 
hall chanting no testing no quarantine no myers no way 
there were no arrests 
indiana law requires the reporting by name of any person who 
tests positive for the human immunodeficiency virus 
the names of infected people are collected and stored in 
confidential files at the state board of health the information is 
used to contact sex partners deemed at risk and to target state 
prevention efforts 
</TEXT>
