an fbi agent and a bank robbery suspect were 
killed and two fbi agents were wounded in a shootout at a home 
friday night authorities said 
the agents who were members of a swat team were executing a 
search warrant about 715 pm in south st louis county when the 
suspect opened fire with a shotgun fbi spokesman david binney said 
the names of the agents werent immediately available the agent 
who was killed was pronounced dead at 9 pm at st anthonys 
hospital binney said 
wounds to the other two agents werent believed to be serious 
one of the agents was shot in the arm and the other was shot in the 
leg both were taken to st anthonys hospital binney said 
the suspect was identified as james price 45 
the agents were looking for money taken in a jan 3 robbery of 
community savings amp loan near prices home binney said 
we used a swat team because we had information that the man 
was armed and dangerous binney said the swat team penetrated 
the door and shooting occurred 
