<TEXT>
marion barry jr was a sharecroppers son who 
used the streetwise bravado he learned as a civil rights activist 
to become a savvy political insider who served more than a decade 
as mayor of the nations capital 
always claiming he could move as easily among royalty as among 
the citys poor barry shrugged off scandals involving top aides 
and allegations of drug abuse to win election three times to the 
citys top position 
during his tenure barry made the most of the limited power of 
the citys home rule charter to make himself the undisputed leader 
of the city government 
but barry was also under federal investigation during much of 
the period between 1984 and 1990 for his ties to drug suspects 
several of his friends have gone to jail and recent news reports 
suggested the wall of silence that prosecutors had tried to 
penetrate was crumbling as some former associates testified before 
a grand jury 
barry has always called himself a survivor pointing to the 
gunshot wound he suffered in the city hall building in 1977 as an 
example of how he could never be counted out 
he is not going to go out quietly said max berry a former 
key political adviser after the arrest 
berry who turned against barry after the mayors troubles last 
year added if he has not been telling the truth to the people 
hes going to face the possibility of resigning but he has always 
been a strong campaigner and a proud person what kind of effect 
this will have on his ego i dont know 
indeed barrys most recent boasts of political power were 
earlier this month 
a los angeles times profile got him into political hot water 
when he was quoted as boasting that he would cut his opponents 
off at the kneecaps and that jesse jackson whom barry had 
supported dont wanna run nothing but his mouth 
barry and his third wife effi have one son christopher who 
is 10 
barry was born on march 6 1936 to marion and mattie barry in 
the small mississippi delta town of itta bena and was raised in 
memphis after the death of his father a sharecropper 
my background is one of survival barry told the washington 
post a month before his first election as mayor in 1978 i mean i 
was lucky you know i used to run around with guys who went to 
prison or are dead i was lucky i was the one who didnt get 
caught by the police when we were out shooting dice or something 
barry did graduate work in chemistry at fisk university in 
nashville but was sidetracked on his way to a doctorate by the 
growing civil rights movement and left school with a masters 
degree he was the first national chairman of the student 
nonviolent coordinating committee which sent young people into 
the south to register black voters 
it was sncc that brought him to washington where he became 
immersed in local issues joining boycotts of the bus system 
with his second wife mary treadwell he helped found a black 
selfhelp group pride inc treadwell was convicted in 1983 of 
misusing funds in connection with a real estate spinoff of pride 
it was barrys high profile as an antiestablishment activist 
that propelled him into local politics first as a member of the 
board of education and then in 1974 as a member of the first 
elected city council organized under the home rule legislation 
he suffered his first personal crisis in 1977 when he was 
wounded by a shotgun blast in the hanafi muslim takeover of the 
district building the districts city hall a young reporter was 
killed 
in 1978 he defeated incumbent mayor walter washington in the 
citys democratic mayoral primary and went on to easily win the 
general election taking over a government he had railed against 
only a decade before 
i want to take the boards off of houses and put people in 
them i want to provide minimal care for all people regardless of 
their financial situation and i want to live out dr martin 
luther kings legacy of peace brotherhood and survival he said 
shortly after being sworn in 
his tenure has been noted for extensive downtown office and 
hotel development a soaring murder rate among young drug users 
and critics charge deterioration of services like housing despite 
the largest city bureaucracy in the country on a percapita basis 
his troubles began shortly after his first reelection in 1982 
with the first of federal investigations he termed attempts to 
lynch black people another way 
in 1984 karen johnson a convicted cocaine dealer with whom 
barry admitted having a personal relationship served 11 months 
in jail on contempt of court charges rather than tell investigators 
whether she used drugs with or sold them to the mayor 
the current round of investigation was touched off in december 
1988 when barry repeatedly visited the hotel room of a suspected 
drug dealer that man charles lewis was later convicted of 
cocaine charges in the virgin islands and has pleaded guilty to a 
drug conspiracy count in washington there have been recent news 
reports that lewis had told prosecutors he had provided drugs to 
the mayor 
</TEXT>
