<TEXT>
south koreas crime rate has declined 
by about a third since the government ordered nightspots to close 
before midnight starting this year police said today 
police reported 7859 crimes nationally in the first half of 
this month down 29 percent from the same period in december 
except for those at tourist hotels terminals and railway 
stations nightspots were ordered to shut down before midnight this 
year in an effort to halt a sudden increase in crime 
police and government officials have raided beer halls discos 
bars cabarets and nightclubs and punished owners who violate the 
new regulations 
</TEXT>
