cutting assistance to all countries including israel and egypt 
so it could be redistributed to countries in eastern europe and 
central america dole proposed a 5 percent cut in aid to each 
country which he said would free 400 million for emerging 
democracies 
when dole discussed his plan with reporters he said bush had 
been informed of his idea and that the president mustve agreed 
with it 
the boost would permit new assistance to eastern european and 
central american countries the sources said they said it also 
would allow the united states to pay the 700 million it owes the 
united nations for membership and peacekeeping expenses and to 
begin rebuilding a new embassy in moscow us officials believe 
the newly constructed embassy there is riddled with soviet 
listening devices 
