<TEXT>
the boeing co plans to reduce its seattlearea 
work force by 5000 people this year although the company has 
record orders for commercial jets with deliveries stretching into 
the next century 
better eastwest relations have cast doubt on the future of 
boeings defense business and fewer production workers are needed 
on the companys 747400 jumbo jets boeing officials said thursday 
boeing wants to build a new widebody jet the 777 but no orders 
have been announced and production startup is at least two years 
away 
the aerospace giant said it hopes to accomplish half the cuts 
through retirement and resignations 
the martin marietta astronautics group also announced plans 
thursday to cut about 200 jobs by the end of february but will 
transfer many workers to other posts within the aerospace giant a 
company spokeswoman said in denver 
positions that cannot be directly tied to a contract will be 
affected and will be eliminated possibly through a combination of 
fulltime and parttime jobs said spokeswoman judy stowell 
a review of business propects for 1990 showed the company needed 
to cut overhead labor costs stowell said the company employes 
about 11500 workers in colorado and other martin divisions employ 
3600 workers 
boeings announcement came about two months after the company 
and union workers settled a 48day strike which was mainly over 
wages and mandatory overtime about 43000 seattle area union 
workers were affected by the strike 
boeing said it will give layoff notices today to about 1900 
employees who might be among some 1700 workers who will lose jobs 
starting march 20 the balance of the workers are to be laid off 
later in the year 
boeing has a backlog of more than 1700 commercial jets worth 
about 85 billion last year it added 10000 employees in the 
puget sound area and was so strapped for production workers on its 
747400 that it borrowed 600 machinists from lockheed 
that startup and certification work has been completed and the 
extra workers are no longer needed boeing said delays and 
uncertainties on other projects especially defense work mean the 
lost jobs cannot be absorbed elsewhere in the company it said 
about 1400 of the 1700 hourly employees to be laid off are at 
the companys everett plant north of seattle where widebody 747s 
