antarctica before heading the difficult final 850 miles of its 
4000mile journey to mirnyy which they hope to reach in early 
march 
after leaving vostok which is at 11500 feet the team will 
encounter deep snow and many crevasses as they travel to mirnyy a 
soviet science station on the continents indian ocean shore 
as the antarctic winter approaches the team expects 
temperatures to drop daily from the current 30 degrees below to as 
low as 80 below 
our team can handle the weather steger said in a recorded 
message sent to the expeditions headquarters it is the lack of 
visibility that will be a major problem if we cant see the trail 
