new yorks metropolitan museum of art 
will help one of europes leastknown art museums the romanian 
national restore a collection damaged by revolution and four 
decades of communist rule 
philippe de montebello director of the metropolitan museum of 
art met with senior cultural officials thursday to assess the 
damage and he said afterward he will try to raise corporate 
support to give the romanians basic materials and equipment 
one way to help may be to exhibit at the met six to eight of the 
best works from the romanian collection which features el grecos 
van eycks and french impressionists de montebello said 
the romanian collection and its museum were severely damaged in 
the revolution that toppled dictator nicolae ceausescu on dec 22 
it also had suffered for years beforehand from lack of funds and 
political manipulation the romanian and american museum officials 
say 
the problems are much greater than the damage caused by the 
revolution said everett fahy the mets chief curator who 
accompanied de montebello due to decades of neglect their 
heritage is disintegrating 
