as fierce fighting erupted toward evening trapping her and other 
loyal workers in the museum 
eventually soldiers arrived they were too late to save 16 
destroyed canvases or to prevent severe damage to at least 20 
others 
under the guidance of cosoveanu and other museum officials who 
braved heavy gunfire to return to the gallery however they moved 
a giant el greco adoration and several other valuable works to 
safety 
a tour of the museum made evident it will take years to repair 
the damage done to romanias finest art collection but the 
revolution has restored to the museum some hope it can once again 
become a national pride 
