mayor marion barry appeared before a federal 
magistrate today on a misdemeanor narcotics charge stemming from a 
federal sting operation that law enforcement officials said caught 
him on videotape buying and smoking crack cocaine 
a federal magistrate ordered barry to appear for a status 
hearing feb 5 and required him to submit to drug testing every 
monday 
court papers filed by federal prosecutors said tests conducted 
on blood and urine samples taken from the mayor following his 
arrest thursday night showed evidence of cocaine ingestion 
barry who has repeatedly denied drug use was in court for 10 
minutes and spoke only his name and swore to appear at the hearing 
he was not asked to enter a plea to the charge of possessing a 
controlled substance crack cocaine in this case the charge 
carries a maximum penalty of one year in jail and a fine of 5000 
his attorney r kenneth mundy told the magistrate that barry 
wanted a jury trial and waived his right to a preliminary hearing 
he said the mayor would plead innocent 
i am going to leave here and go about the business of 
government barry told reporters outside the courthouse after the 
hearing he declined to discuss his legal or political future 
top city officials said barrys plans to launch his campaign for 
a fourth term on sunday were being postponed indefinitely four 
current or former city officials already were lined up to run 
against the embattled mayor and jesse jackson also was understood 
to be considering entering the race 
