army member argued friday that the justice department overstepped 
the law in its efforts to deport the man to northern ireland 
the hearing before the 2nd us circuit court of appeals was the 
latest proceeding in joe dohertys highly publicized 6year legal 
battle to fight extradition and deportation 
if he loses doherty could be returned to face life in prison 
for the 1980 killing of a british army captain and a later prison 
escape doherty 34 has been imprisoned since his arrest at a 
manhattan bar in june 1983 
the british government maintains doherty is a common criminal 
