countrys marine corps the air force will lose six squadrons and 
retire five classes of aircraft 
president fw de klerk announced recently that south africa 
would reduce its defense forces because of declining tension in 
southern african and a need to redirect government spending to 
social welfare projects 
the defense budget is about 4 billion annually there were no 
figures on how much money would be saved by the cuts 
south africa last year ended its involvement in a 23year bush 
war against nationalist guerrillas in namibia by agreeing to end 
its rule of the territory namibia is scheduled to become 
indpendent soon probably in march 
south africa also withdrew its forces in 1988 from angola where 
it fought alongside rebels battling the marxist government 
lt gen kat liebenberg acting chief of the defense force said 
the cuts would make the military smaller and more economical but 
would not seriosuly reduce south africas ability to defend itself 
the defense forces will justifiably remain true to its 
reputation as a formidable fighting force that would compel any 
military force in southern africa to think twice before embarking 
on military adventures against our country liebenberg said 
the army the strongest arm of the defense forces with 75000 
troops is least affected by the cuts and will remain the strongest 
military force in africa neighboring black african states have 
much smaller weaker armies 
liebenberg said south africa still needed strong defense forces 
despite the reduction in tension in the region the threat to 
south africa has not totally disappeared he said 
the big cut involving the army was the cancellation of 11 major 
weapons systems under development the statement said another 49 
projects were reduced or delayed he said 
army operating costs will be drastically curtailed the 
statement said 
the navy the smallest arm of the military was hardest hit by 
the cuts with the closing of five naval bases disbanding of the 
900man marine corps and dismantling of the main regional naval 
commands 
liebenberg said 2000 naval personnel out of a force of about 
9000 would be dismissed or retired the south african navy is 
mainly a coastal defense force except for three submarines and two 
older frigates 
