speaking to the global forum on the environment and development 
for survival attended by more than 1000 political and religious 
leaders from around the world gorbachev also backed suggestions 
for the formation of an international relief agency to respond to 
ecological disasters 
he dubbed it the green cross in an obvious reference to the 
red cross 
noting that his own countrys environment has suffered greatly 
from thoughtless decisions gorbachev suggested international 
technical cooperation in preventing and repairing ecological 
damage he added that he is prepared to allow inspections on soviet 
territory to avoid any suspicion that high technology is being 
diverted to other uses 
the soviet union has only begun to recognize its own 
environmental problems in recent years since gorbachevs policy of 
glasnost or openness permitted public criticism of bureaucratic 
decisions 
the soviet environmental movement expanded dramatically after 
the chernobyl nuclear power plant explosion which devastated a 
large area of the ukraine and byelorussia 
gorbachev drew sustained applause from his audience in the grand 
kremlin palace when he repeated the soviet unions longstanding 
offer to end nuclear weapons testing if the united states agrees to 
follow suit 
