funding for imperial ascension ceremonies scheduled later this year 
in 1988 a rightist group claimed responsibility for a shotgun 
attack on the home of the founder of the recruit co a 
conglomerate at the center of a stocktrading scandal that rocked 
the governing liberal democratic party 
rightist groups around the country are thought to have links 
through which they coordinate policy and activities for example 
their decision to halt most public activities during hirohitos 
long illness as a sign of respect and the gathering of dozens of 
sound trucks from around the country in nagasaki to protest 
motoshimas remarks 
rightist groups also are generally thought to be funded by 
underworld yakuza gangs and to receive guns from them but the 
connections remain murky 
many rightists advocate a return to the prewar imperial system 
in which the emperor was considered the nations divine spiritual 
leader and power was highly centralized 
they also want to revise the postwar constitution especially 
article 9 which renounces war and the use of force to settle 
international disputes 
despite their use of the emperor as a symbol many rightist 
groups are not enthusiastic about current emperor akihito whom 
