society observers say in a shock for the rightists akihito also 
pledged when he became emperor to uphold the constitution 
in contrast the imperial system has been a focus of attacks by 
japans leftist extremists officials say they plan to mobilize 
about 32000 police to guard the imperial ascension ceremonies from 
possible leftist attack this fall 
