vice minister of the state science and technology commission 
matsuuras visit follows the lifting of martial law in beijing 
last week a move aimed at easing tensions with the united states 
and other countries and persuading the west to end sanctions on 
badly needed soft loans for development projects 
the united state responded to the lifting of martial law by 
saying it would support new world bank loans for humanitarian 
purposes japan also welcomed the end of martial law but said it 
