the visit to the three women saying it was part of a wider 
investigation but he denied an allegation by burstyn that the ins 
agents accused the women of involvement in moneylaundering to 
frighten them into silence 
the ins did have an ongoing investigation about alien 
smuggling which touched on del cid the prosecutor said we 
were seeking information about this family 
and even if no such investigation existed sullivan said the 
government has an absolute right to question witnesses 
the acting director of the local immigration and naturalization 
services richard smith said he could not comment on the case 
without authorization from washington 
after the hearing burstyn said he was satisfied with the 
judges action 
del cid a lieutenant colonel in the panamanian defense force at 
the time of his arrest just after the us invasion of panama 
faces a maximum 70 years imprisonment and 550000 in fines if 
convicted of being a liaison and courier between noriega and drug 
traffickers 
