<TEXT>
federal prosecutors dismissed suggestions 
friday that mayor marion barry was the victim of entrapment when he 
was videotaped by fbi agents buying and smoking crack cocaine 
but legal experts and federal law enforcement officials say 
barry may have no choice in the face of overwhelming evidence he 
used drugs to claim the government improperly lured him to a hotel 
room where bought and smoked crack 
us attorney jay b stephens said that the carefully planned 
carefully reviewed and carefully executed undercover operation 
was scrupulously fair to the defendant mr barry 
there was no entrapment there stephens told reporters on 
the steps of the us courthouse after barry appeared before a 
federal magistrate on a misdemeanor charge of possessing crack 
cocaine 
prosecutors examined evidence gathered in the yearlong 
investigation of allegations that barry used drugs and decided an 
undercover operation would comply with the law stephens said 
while not commenting specifically on the evidence against barry 
stephens indicated that his office had gathered evidence that the 
mayor was predisposed toward drug use 
where there is predisposition there is no entrapment the 
citys chief prosecutor said citing the supreme courts test on 
the issue 
the entrapment defense that law enforcement authorities led a 
defendant to commit a crime he otherwise wouldnt have committed 
must be raised by the accused at trial the high court has ruled 
that a defendant is the victim of entrapment if not predisposed to 
commit the crime that undercover police induced him to commit 
stephens cited evidence that barry went to the vista hotel on 
his own volition 
he went to the seventh floor on his own free will he put 
himself in that situation the prosecutor said 
as further indication of the governments confidence in the 
case justice department spokesman david runkel said attorney 
general dick thornburgh followed the progress of the undercover 
investigation up through barrys arrest thursday evening at a 
downtown hotel 
as a defense entrapment is difficult to raise but it has been 
successful notably in automaker john z deloreans 1984 acquittal 
of federal drug conspiracy charges 
de loreans lawyers were able to persuade jurors the automaker 
was entrapped by federal agents despite videotapes showing the 
defendant standing next to open suitcase filled with cocaine and 
saying its good as gold 
but given the strength of the governments evidence barrys 
defense would have to be entrapment even though it will be 
impossible to sell to a jury said peter tague a law professor 
at georgetown university 
an entrapment defense would open the door for government 
prosecutors to present evidence of his predisposition to use 
illegal drugs tague said 
tague said prosecutors would be free to present testimony by 
convicted drug dealer charles lewis that he sold cocaine to the 
mayor and used it with him at a downtown hotel in 1988 
even though barry was never charged as a result of that 
incident prosecutors could use lewis statements as evidence the 
mayor was predisposed to using illegal drugs tague said 
stephens statements indicated that prosecutors were ready for 
such a defense with evidence aplenty of the mayors 
predisposition toward illegal drug use 
before launching the undercover sting we reviewed all the 
evidence we developed to date stephens said 
but if barry can evoke enough sympathy among jurors he could 
persuade them he was the victim of government zeal to catch him 
experts said 
the jury can always say this guy was not willing to commit a 
crime and the government went way too far in importuning him 
tague said 
unlike de lorean barry would be accountable to more than just 
12 jurors he must answer to voters of the nations capital where 
he had been expected to announce plans to run for a fourth term 
