<TEXT>
while making her first feature film 
sweetie jane campion was too busy to critique the story any 
message this dark comedy might carry was left to the medium itself 
the new zealandborn director saw herself as a pragmatist a 
problemsolver who used intuition rather than ideals to make 
creative decisions only upon viewing the film did she permit 
herself the luxury of a little instant analysis 
it was a surprise to me the 34yearold director said in an 
interview for me it was a personal experience when i saw it i 
thought there are things i wasnt expecting 
i was really rewarded by the effort i felt really high on 
occasion when some notes hit that were really special i always 
want the possibility that there is some surprise for you that 
something unique will happen 
with most of the cast and crew working on its first feature film 
as well sweetie does seem to unfold at its own unaffected 
pace as gentle as the trees that provided meaning for the films 
tortured australian family as dark as the lipstick worn by the 
title character 
based on an original story by campion and australian author 
gerard lee sweetie is minimalism from down under days of rage 
and days of detachment brought to theaters for a mere 13 million 
the screen for this small intimate film is filled literally 
by sweetie played by firsttime actress genevieve lemon paranoid 
