likening its newscasts to the straightahead cbs evening news 
when walter cronkite anchored it 
cnn is doing the basic nuts and bolts of news the way cronkite 
used to do it moyers says venturing that in time ted turners 
24hour cnn will be the staple of most people 
the primary reason he says is that our work habits travel 
schedules and living habits are such now that its very hard to 
create a critical mass of audience at a given time so you have to 
be there when people want you 
will network evening newscasts eventually go the way of the 
pterodactyl moyers the former commentator on those of cbs 
doesnt know 
its hard to fathom the thinking of the people who are in 
charge of the networks now he says as long as they are making 
money out of it i think they will continue what theyre doing 
but i find it hard to believe that all three of them can be 
making money out of newscasts that are essentially alike 
</TEXT>
