<TEXT>
from stettin in the baltic to trieste in the adriatic an iron 
curtain has descended across the continent 
so declared winston churchill on march 5 1946 in a speech to 
westminster college in fulton mo 
behind that line lie all the capitals of the ancient states of 
central and eastern europe he said 
the wartime british prime minister had it almost right as 
things later turned out the iron curtain started at the west 
german port of travemuende on the baltic sea about 150 miles west 
of the polish port of stettin in 1946 the division of germany 
into separate states was not yet envisaged stettin now szczecin 
lies near what is today the eastern border of east germany 
churchill did not coin the term iron curtain a british 
newspaper had used it the year before to define europes postworld 
war ii ideological divide but it was churchills speech that 
popularized it as an image of the cold war 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

