<TEXT>
while many fellow economists are contemplating a 
soft landing if not a recession for the economy in 1990 russell 
redenbaugh an experienced forecaster is preparing for a soft 
takeoff 
a soft takeoff is a safe one although perhaps undramatic it is 
not a sudden ascent its characteristics are moderation 
sustainability steadiness it is a positive reassuring economy 
in more specific economic terms it means growth of between 2 
percent and 3 percent accompanied by moderation of the extremes 
and negatives that marred the 1980s 
it means lower inflation lower interest rates a lower federal 
budget deficit it means more exports and a reduction in the trade 
imbalance it is one accompanied by lower capital gains taxes and 
rising returns on capital 
it is an economic situation that redenbaugh says professional 
economists with a negative outlook have grossly misread 
because they have misread events he says they have come to 
patently wrong conclusions 
that is they are talking about economic deterioration obsessed 
with a handful of gloomy statistics for specific sectors of the 
us economy unable to measure an historic event that he calls 
the key indicator 
to him the key to the immediate economic future is the freeing 
of the eastern european economies from 40 years of 
deindustrialization a discontinuity that the economics 
profession cannot comprehend 
redenbaugh knows that his forecast puts him way out on a limb 
especially in the conservative business in which he operates but 
he claims to like it there saying i feel comfortable its never 
crowded 
most economists and investment advisers run in a herd he says 
adding in this business you must have an aversion to crowds 
crowds are comfortable but they never produce good results 
redenbaugh needs results is measured by them and expects to 
get them as chief strategist for cooke amp bieler inc a 
philadelphiabased asset management firm for fortune 500 pension 
funds and profitsharing accounts 
he believes that recent economic events will produce a real 
peace dividend an immediate expansion of commerce and a 
lengthening investment horizon that as a consequence will means 
higher priceearnings ratios for stocks 
he isnt entirely alone in his optimism edward yardeni of 
prudentialbache is probably as far out on a limb and the 
conference board said today that the us economy is rebounding 
rather than eroding with exports leading the way 
but if you attended a convention of economists almost anywhere 
this month you might not be pleased with what you heard based on 
their published reports almost any uplifting news would be 
balanced off with depressing reminders 
redenbaugh believes many professional economists are unable to 
deal with changes in europe because it doesnt fit their 
orthodoxy of using statistical models to explain everything 
he contends they want to say something to the effect that 
three out of the last four times when the iron curtain collapsed 
the following happened which is of course absurd 
while the suddenness of the collapse of managed economies in 
europe amazed redenbaugh he had suggested it might happen 
although more slowly in a paper one year ago 
at that time he said economic considerations were dismantling 
the iron curtain and undermining communist ideology and that if 
the soviet union was to survive it would have to abandon marxist 
economic systems 
what has since occurred he says is now the key factor in 
economic forecasting whether or not it fits the conventional 
forecasting models 
as the 1990s begin he states it is not the health of the 
economy that is questionable for it is healthy it is the health 
of the economics profession that is questionable 
</TEXT>
