association of homebuilders that congress must adopt fiscal 
policies as sound as those of the average american household 
bushs comments added impetus to administration efforts to 
pressure the federal reserve board into an easier credit policy 
we cannot allow the high costs of housing to suffocate the 
financial life of americas young people the president said 
when it comes to housing this must not become a society of haves 
and havenots 
observing that the cost of new homes has been steadily 
increasing for the past decade and a half bush said more and 
more young americans are finding themselves priced out of the home 
market 
he vowed to work with housing secretary jack kemp to cut federal 
red tape to create decent housing that people can afford 
he noted that he had asked kemp to convene a commission that 
would study burdensome bureaucratic barriers to affordable housing 
construction and make recommendations on how to eliminate them 
he offered no details 
but the truth is theres one housing policy and one sales 
strategy thats better than all others combined a healthy growing 
economy with low longterm interest rates bush declared 
vital to homebuyer and homebuilder alike are low and stable 
rates of interest the president added claiming that each 
increase of one percentage point in the interest rate knocks 
millions of families out of the market 
bushs comments and those by other administration officials come 
amid speculation that momentum at the fed for easing credit policy 
had ended 
as he has done in nearly all of his speeches this year bush 
also called on congress to act on items that he proposed last year 
especially his proposal for a cut in the tax rate on capital gains 
the profit from sales of investments 
i call on the democrat leaders of congress to give the 
american people a break and to let the house and senate work their 
will by having an upanddown vote on the capital gains tax cut 
bush said 
he also the homebuilders organization that he stands firm in his 
opposition to massive new government public housing projects and 
will press again in the upcoming session of congress for a plan to 
give public housing tenants vouchers to make it easier for them to 
buy their own units 
bush made a special point of praising former president carter 
and his wife rosalynn as a point of light for working with an 
organization that helps provide lowcost shelter 
the president also departed from his prepared text to tell the 
homeowners that he was annoyed to see so many suburbs denuded of 
trees when builders clear new tracts and subdivisions and asked 
them to save some both for the sake of business and for the 
environment 
several hecklers holding a sign protesting us aid to the 
government of el salvador jeered bush briefly from the back of the 
hall before being led away by security officers 
bush took note of a planned white supremacist march saturday 
near the martin luther king center in atlanta 
atlanta is a great cheerful city that has proudly risen from 
the ashes of a distant past he said and for those who plan to 
revel in a rally of hate here tomorrow let them know this 
atlantans like all americans turn their backs on bigots 
following his speech in atlantas omni coliseum the president 
was flying to florida for a lateafternoon tour and briefing at 
everglades national park and to speak at a fundraising dinner in 
miami for republican gov bob martinezs reelection campaign 
on thursday white house press secretary marlin fitzwater urged 
lower interest rates breaking the administrations general policy 
of not commenting on fed policy 
this is not a new message but its important occasionally to 
point out that lower interest rates are normally good for the 
economy he said 
furthermore he said fed members should take a close look at 
recent economic indicators which show moderate inflation and 
sluggishness in retail sales and housing and understand these 
numbers are low and indicate inflation has remained very steady 
over the last seven or eight years and that lower interest rates 
are justified 
the administrations statement on interest rate policy comes 
amid speculation that momentum for lower rates at the fed had ended 
no one would welcome lower rates more than the homebuilders who 
have just finished their worst year since the recession of 1982 
the housing industry was sluggish through most of 1989 as the 
fed pushed up interest rates as it sought to slow the economy and 
curtail inflation 
as concerns grew that the economy might be slowing too much the 
fed allowed interest rates to gradually fall in recent months but 
not by enough to help the homebuilding industry 
david seiders chief economist for the organization bush was 
addressing said he is counting on a moderate decline in interest 
rates in the first half of the year to sustain his organizations 
forecast for a better year this year 
the commerce department on thursday reported that housing starts 
construction begun on new homes and apartments tumbled by 8 
percent in december the worst performance since october 1982 
fitzwater said the plunge was not good news although 
analysts blamed much of the drop on unseasonably cold weather in 
much of the nation 
