the claim accuses broker walter kovler himself around 80 years 
old with unsuitable and unsupervised trading in speculative stock 
options using the conservative stockandbond portfolio she brought 
to the wall street firm 
mrs willdorffs case typifies disputes resolved out of court in 
arbitration before a panel usually consisting of two independent 
arbitrators and one from the securities industry 
this is the horror that occurred to thousands of unwitting 
small investors who will never be able to recover from what 
happened in 1987 said attorney theodore eppenstein mrs 
willdorff went from a millionaire to insolvency in a few weeks 
when mrs willdorff opened her account she signed a contract 
requiring her to submit any grievance to arbitration forfeiting 
the right to sue the supreme court last year upheld such contracts 
mrs willdorff will be bound by the decision of the arbitration 
panel with limited rights of appeal studies show investors win 
about half their cases and victorious plaintiffs recover about half 
their losses 
eppenstein who unsuccessfully argued the supreme court case on 
arbitrations contracts said that given the size of the claim he 
would have sued shearson rather than arbitrate 
theodore a krebsbach shearsons litigation director declined 
to comment because arbitration proceedings are supposed to be 
private i think any claimant would be upset with us if we went 
public with the facts of a case that was pending he said 
