<TEXT>
the house judiciary committee will investigate 
the bankruptcy filings by campeau corps us retail divisions and 
look into the consequences of leveraged buyouts chairman jack 
brooks announced friday 
brooks dtexas said the judiciary subcommittee on economic and 
commercial law would hold hearings on the courtsupervised 
reorganization of federated stores inc the renamed holding 
company of campeaus us operations and the potential for a wave 
of new bankruptcies resulting from debtfinanced takeovers in 
recent years 
the gold rush is over now and the time for reassessment has 
arrived i intend to move quickly in the upcoming session of 
congress to consider the lessons of the campeau bankruptcy and how 
lbo bankruptcies will affect consumers suppliers creditors and 
the american economy brooks said 
swamped by debt campeaus federated department stores inc and 
allied stores corp divisions filed for protection from creditors 
under chapter 11 of the us bankruptcy act on monday the 258 
stores run by federated and allied will remain open while the court 
oversees their restructuring 
torontobased campeaus acquisition of federated in 1988 and 
allied in 1986 left the two saddled with 77 billion in debt 
together federated and allied run nine department store chains such 
as bloomingdales burdines jordan marsh richs and lazarus 
with campeaus bankruptcy in the first days of the 1990s our 
nation has begun to reap the bitter harvest of the leveraged buyout 
frenzy of the 1980s said brooks who is also chairman of the 
subcommittee which has jurisdiction over competition policy as 
well as bankruptcy law 
i fear that the campeau chapter 11 filing in cincinnati this 
week is only the beginning and that we will see the takeover 
trophies of the 1980s become the bankruptcy case names of the 
1990s brooks said 
</TEXT>
