federal regulators on friday denied 
californias home savings of america the largest and one of the 
healthiest thrift institutions in the nation permission to switch 
to the insurance fund backing commercial bank deposits 
home savings whose deposits are insured by the savings 
association insurance fund had applied to merge with its 
whollyowned subsidiary bowery savings bank of new york which is 
already insured by the bank insurance fund members of the savings 
fund pay higher deposit insurance premiums than members of the bank 
fund 
