<TEXT>
after some mixed signals from federal 
regulators earlier this month the nations five options exchanges 
are set to begin trading on new listings monday 
but most exchanges will be offering new options on far fewer 
stocks than originally planned because the securities and exchange 
commission which regulates options hasnt changed its rules yet 
options are financial instruments that give holders that right 
to buy or sell 100 shares of a stock at a designated price for a 
certain amount of time 
options are traded on stocks listed on exchanges or traded over 
the counter 
currently most options on the stocks listed on an exchange can 
only be traded in one marketplace at a time the privilege of 
trading a specific option assigned by lottery is not permitted on 
any other exchange 
but thanks to a rule passed by the sec last may that 
exclusivity will end on jan 22 
the new sec rule will allow for the multiple listing of all 
options 
but earlier this month sec chairman richard c breeden asked 
the exchanges to voluntarily limit their multiple listings to new 
options while maintaining the exclusivity of listings for existing 
options 
breeden asked the exchanges to delay phasing in the existing 
options until june to allow development of some way to link all the 
markets so investors can have access to the best deal 
the allocation plan or lottery is abolished as of monday for 
new options said bonnie greenberg of the chicago board options 
exchange the worlds biggest options exchange 
on monday the american stock exchange in new york will list 
options in the stock of fleetnorstar financial group inc racal 
telecom plc and sothebys holdings plc 
options on sothebys also will be offered on the cboe and the 
pacific stock exchange 
but all of those exchanges had planned to list many more 
options expecting new rules that would lower the eligibility 
requirements for stocks to have options listed the sec however 
informed the exchanges earlier this month that the lower 
requirements hadnt been approved yet and the old standards were 
still in effect 
we intended to trade 31 options if certain requirements were 
met said roy berces a spokesman for the pacific stock exchange 
instead he said the pacific exchange will be listing just three 
options norwest corp sundstrand corp and sothebys 
the other options exchanges in this country are the new york 
stock exchange and the philadelphia stock exchange 
</TEXT>
